<promed@promedmail.org>
[Ross River virus is classified in the 7th Report of the ICTV as a
constituent species of the genus _Alphavirus_ of the family _Togaviridae_.
Epidemics of benign polyarthritis associated with Ross River virus
infection, involving several thousand of cases, occur regularly in
Australia. The virus is endemic in most costal regions, and inland along the
course of rivers. Since 1980, Ross River virus has been reported from a
number of south Pacific islands. Several species of mosquito are implicated
as vectors. Barmah Forest virus is a serologically distinct alphavirus that
produces a similar but milder polyarthritis. - Mod.CP
